Variable : Variables  are used to store the data(number, String, boolean, float, double).

Data Type : Specifies the size and type of the value stored in variable.

            1.primitive data types(byte,short,int,float,double,boolean and char).
            2.non primitive data types(String, Classes etc...) .
            
   Data types are required so that you know what "kind" of data your variable holds,
    or can hold. If you (and compiler, and runtime and what not) know this information 
    in advance, you can save a hell lot of runtime issues at compile time only.

       
NamingConventions :

Class :

class name should start with UpperCase letter, should be noun

ex:
1. class Bank{


}   

2.  class AccountDetails {

}

3.  class Employee {

}
======================
method : method name should start with lowerCase letter,should be verb.

1. public void saveAccountDetails(){

}
2. public void deleteAccount(){}

3. public void updateAccount(){}
=====================

variableName : variable name should start with lower case letter


ex: String studentName;
    String accountNumber;
    
    
====================

identifier(class , method or variable) should not start with number or special character except $ or _.

int 123Age // invalid
String #name // invalid
String %per  // invalid
String _accountNumber // valid
String $price // valid


Task 1 : Write 10 Valid and Invalid identifiers (class , methods, variables)
Task 2 : Write 10 valid and Invalid naming convention identifiers.










    

             




